{"name":"Infused Warmth","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_pyro.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You are less affected by weather </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">– </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">the heat is less taxing, and your increased body temperature helps you against the cold.</span></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Fireweaving Tier</span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\"> <strong>2:</strong> </span>Your Infused Warmth improves. You may burn a creature grappling you, dealing <span class=\"fontstyle0\">fire damage equal to your Constitution modifier. This damage is taken when you have been successfully grappled and then at the start of each of your grappler</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">’</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">s turns that it maintains the grapple.</span> </p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"psionics"},"requirements":"Pyrofusist","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"0dKzwXG5vS6ZZj5q"}
{"name":"Inflict Pain Tier 2","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_blood.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You use your own vitality to boil the blood of those around you. All creatures within 15 feet of you must make a Constitution saving throw or take 3d6 necrotic damage per Bloodweaving tier. If any of these creatures bears your Seeker</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">’</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">s Mark, you heal for half the damage it takes (rounded down).</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>Critical success</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You take necrotic damage equal to twice your Constitution modifier.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>Success</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The creature takes half damage. </span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>Critical failure</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The creature gains one level of exhaustion.</span> </li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":"HD: 2, Verbal"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"con","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["6d6","necrotic"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"con"},"requirements":"Bloodfussit","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"0u6ABsXHISRyIf3p"}
{"name":"Bubble Cage","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_hydro.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You create a 5-foot diameter rolling sphere of churning water that can engulf those it strikes. The orb can move up to 30 feet per round while on a solid horizontal surface, rolling over barriers less than 10 feet tall. When you activate this ability, you can also move it up to 30 feet so long as it remains within range, and on each of your subsequent turns for the duration, you can use a bonus action to move the orb this same distance. If you do not do so, the bubble cage merely stays at rest and churns in place. It automatically quenches any fires that it can encompass fully. A bubble cage stops if it moves outside the ability</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">’</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">s range.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><br />The orb lasts a number of rounds equal to your Waterweaving tier. You can extend the duration of the orb by expending 1 Hit Die when you activate this ability, allowing the orb to remain for an additional number of rounds equal to your Constitution modifier.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><br />Your Waterweaving tier also allows you to increase the size of the orb. At tier II, you can spend an additional mana to make the orb 10 feet. At tier III, you can spend a total of 3 mana to make the orb 15 feet in diameter.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><br />Any creature in the path of the orb must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failure, it takes 2d6 points of bludgeoning damage and is engulfed by the bubble cage and carried along with it. Engulfed creatures are immersed in water and must hold their breath unless capable of breathing water. They gain cover against attacks from outside the orb but are considered entangled by its churning currents. Creatures also take 2d6 points of damage at the beginning of their turn each round they remain trapped. Creatures within the orb may attempt a new Dexterity save each round to escape into a random square adjacent to the bubble cage.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><br />Depending on what tier of bubble cage you activated, your orb can hold varying sizes and numbers of creatures. A tier I bubble cage can hold up to 1 Medium, 2 Small, or 4 smaller creatures  within it. At tier II, it can hold 1 Large, 4 Medium, or 16 Small or smaller creatures within it. At tier III, the orb may hold 1 Huge creature, 2 Large creatures, 8 Medium, or 32 Small or smaller creatures within it.</span></p>\n<p><br /><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>Synergy</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If you have affinity with other infusions, you can alter your bubble cage. To use a synergy, you must decide select it upon activating this ability.</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Aerofusion </strong>turns the bubble cage to ice. The orb now deals 2d6 bludgeoning damage and 2d6 cold damage to creatures in its path, but it does not capture creatures within it. Creatures can still attempt a Dexterity saving throw to avoid this damage. As a bonus action or at the end of the ability</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">’</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">s duration, you can force your ice orb to explode in a 20-foot radius burst, dealing 6d6 cold damage to each creature in the area that fails a Dexterity saving throw. On a success, creatures take half this damage.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Bloodfusion </strong>transforms the bubble cage into a bloody orb that drains the lifeforce out of creatures. It acts as the standard bubble cage, but so long as you are within the range of the orb, you heal half the damage that creatures take while entangled in the orb. </span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Pyrofusion </strong>heats the bubble cage, scalding creatures within and around it. It acts as the standard bubble cage with the following addition: creatures adjacent to the orb</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">’</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">s path take fire damage equal to your Constitution modifier. Creatures captured within take an additional 2d6 fire damage.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":"Mana: 1*, Somatic"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"spec"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":30,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"con","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d6","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"con"},"requirements":"Hydrofusist","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"1HkutrUbMmmgMHoY"}
{"name":"Create Water","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_hydro.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You draw water motes out of the air and condense them into a pool of water. You must spend 1 minute and expend 1 Hit Die to create one allon of potable water within 15 feet of you. You can target a vessel that you can see or else the water forms on the ground, saturating it.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><br />Alternatively, you can purify double the amount of water from an available source.</span> </p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;color:#191813;font-size:13px\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">Waterweaving Tier 2: </strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"> </span><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Your Create Water improves. By spending 10 minutes and 3 Hit Die, you can create a 5-foot cube of water (roughly 37 gallons). If you are purifying water, you double this amount.</span></span><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"> <br style=\"font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;font-weight:normal;line-height:normal;text-align:-webkit-auto;text-size-adjust:auto\" /></strong></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">Waterweaving Tier 3: </strong> Y<span class=\"fontstyle0\">our Create Water improves. By spending 1 hour and 5 Hit Die, you create a 10-foot cube of water (roughly 75 gallons). If you are purifying water, you double this amount.</span> </li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"minute","cost":1,"condition":"HD: 1, Somatic, Verbal"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"spec"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":15,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"psionics"},"requirements":"Hydrofusist","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"2Wk52fZerRx7TqVm"}
{"name":"Torrent","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_hydro.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You push forth a powerful stream of water that batters all creatures and obstacles in its path. Your torrential stream is a 30-foot line that is 5 feet wide and 10 feet tall and runs along a solid surface. Loose, unattended objects that are Medium or smaller are pushed along the stream and possibly destroyed. Similarly sized plants are uprooted, and fires along the torrent are extinguished.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><br />Creatures caught in the torrent must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes 5d10 bludgeoning damage and is tossed to an adjacent space next to the torrent. If the creature Huge or smaller, is knocked prone and is dazed until the end of its next turn. A creature dazed in this manner suffers disadvantage on its next attack or saving throw, whichever comes first.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><br />If you do not have a water source of at least 10 cubic feet within range, your cost for this infusion increases by 1 Hit Die for each 5 cubic feet missing as you must drain and gather all possible water motes to activate the ability. </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Critical success</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A creature takes no damage and suffers no effects. </span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Save</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A creature takes half the damage and does not move or fall prone. </span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Critical fail</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The creature is stunned until the end of its next turn.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><br /></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Empower</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If you have affinity to other infusions, you can spend 1 additional mana to enhance the torrent in following ways. A torrent can only have one enhancement.</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Aerofusion</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can add 2d6 cold damage per Windweaving tier you mastered, and after the torrent dissipates, the water hardens to ice on the ground that lasts for 1 hour. The area is considered difficult terrain.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Bloodfusion</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Creatures who fail the saving throw against your torrent also suffer 1 level of exhaustion. A creature can only suffer 1 level of exhaustion with this ability.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Pyrofusion</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can add 1d6 fire damage per Fireweaving tier you mastered, and after the torrent dissipates, the water turns to steam. This </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">creates an area of blistering, concealing mist that fills the line and spaces adjacent to it. Attacks made in the mist or through it are done so at disadvantage, and a creature suffers fire damage equal to your Constitution modifier each time it begins its turn and enters a space with steam. The steam remains a number of turns equal to your Constitution modifier.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><br /></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Synergy</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If you also have affinity to other infusions, you can alter your torrent. If you have selected an enhancement through the Empower options, you must select the same type for this synergy.</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Aerofusion </strong>makes the water freezing cold, adding cold damage equal to your Constitution modifier.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Bloodfusion </strong>turns the water bracken and dark, adding necrotic damage equal to your Constitution modifier.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Pyrofusion </strong>superheats the water, adding fire damage equal to your Constitution modifier.</span> </li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":"HD: 2*, Mana: 2, Somatic"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":30,"width":5,"units":"ft","type":"line"},"range":{"value":60,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"con","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["5d10","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"con"},"requirements":"Hydrofusist","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.f7kfMUEPPEYlbV2G"}},"_id":"4b9JtPoMYbN2Dw7T"}
{"name":"Flame Arrows Tier 2","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_pyro.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Fire motes transform ammunition (such as arrows, crossbow bolts, and sling stones) into fiery projectiles. Each piece of ammunition deals an extra 1d6 points of fire damage to any target it hits. A flaming projectile can easily ignite a flammable object or structure, but it won't ignite a creature it strikes. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Empower</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">While this ability is active, you can use a bonus action and spend 1 mana to turn your shot into a burst. Your shot deals damage as normal but also creates a burst of fire. All creatures within 10 feet of your target must make a Dexterity save or take 1d6 fire damage per Fireweaving tier you have mastered. </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Success</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Creatures take half damage.</span> </li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":"HD: 1, Somatic"},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"con","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d6","fire"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"con"},"requirements":"Pyrofusist","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"7BfxLO7uanOxdCAb"}
{"name":"Hydrospear","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_hydro.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You concentrate water into a powerful jet to spear your enemy. You must have an adequate water source such as a ration of water held in a  waterskin. Make a ranged infusion attack at one creature you can see within range. On a hit, your spear deals 1d6 piercing damage per point in your pool (maximum 5), and the water is spent.</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Miss</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The water splashes harmlessly against your target and is lost unless you can spend 1 minute in a focused state to collect it.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Critical hit</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Your hydrospear also deals splash damage. Any creature within 5 feet of your target takes piercing damage equal to your Constitution modifier. </span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Synergy</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If you also have affinity to other infusions, you can alter your hydrospear.</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Aerofusion </strong>transforms the spear into solid ice and deals additional cold damage equal to your Constitution modifier.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Bloodfusion </strong>alters the water to become toxic and adds necrotic damage equal to your Constitution modifier.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Pyrofusion </strong>superheats the water and deals fire damage equal to your Constitution modifier.</span> </li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":"Mana Pool: 1-5, Somatic"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":60,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"con","actionType":"rwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"psionics"},"requirements":"Hydrofusist","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"96xBA4FJK8oJhm7J"}
{"name":"Wind Stream","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_aero.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">As an action, you blow out a stream of focused air from yourself that is 30 feet long and 5 feet wide. You can aim this line vertically or horizontally, and each creature in that area must make a Strength saving throw or take 2d6 bludgeoning damage per mana spent.</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Critical success</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Creature is unaffected.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Success</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Creature takes half damage. </span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Failure</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A creature up to one size category larger than you or smaller is knocked prone. If the creature is flying, it falls 20 feet instead.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Critical failure</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Creature takes double damage.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Empower</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If you maintain a mana pool of 1, you can hold concentration on this Wind Stream for up to 1 minute. Each turn after triggering the stream, you can spend a bonus action to reshape the stream. The stream no longer deals bludgeoning damage on these subsequent turns, but it can still knock creatures prone. In addition, you can move through your stream once per turn, immediately traveling from the beginning to the end of it. Other Aerofusists can also travel through the stream in the same manner. If your stream is blocked by an obstacle, you stop at that point. If you stop in air, you fall immediately unless you have another mechanism to stay aloft. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><br /></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Synergy</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If you hold concentration on this ability, any infusions from yourself or allies besides Aerofusion can target the stream. The infusion triggers through the stream or at any point of the stream (fusist</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">’</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">s choice). An enemy fusist attempting to use your stream must make a Constitution save against your DC. On a success, the fusist can access your stream.</span> </p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":"Mana: 1-3, Verbal"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":30,"width":5,"units":"ft","type":"line"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d6","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"str","dc":null,"scaling":"con"},"requirements":"Aerofusist","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"AzE08hMafZp8z8bH"}
{"name":"Airburst","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_aero.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can use a bonus action to create an airburst from your hands or feet, propelling you 30 feet in a direction of your choice. You must have an unobstructed path, or your propulsion is halted. You cannot activate this ability if you are encumbered. After moving, you fall to the ground, ignoring the first 30 feet of falling damage.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><br />If you use this airburst while flying, levitating, or hovering, you are not forced to fall so long as you can maintain your height otherwise. Airburst can be used while underwater to help with movement.</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Windweaving Tier 3:</strong> Y</span>our Airburst now moves you 40 feet and after using a burst, you <span class=\"fontstyle0\">may ignore the first 40 feet of falling damage.</span> </li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":"Mana Pool: 1, Somatic"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":30,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"psionics"},"requirements":"Aerofusist","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"B593VEvYEQ3vbPD3"}
{"name":"Inflict Pain Tier 3","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_blood.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You use your own vitality to boil the blood of those around you. All creatures within 15 feet of you must make a Constitution saving throw or take 3d6 necrotic damage per Bloodweaving tier. If any of these creatures bears your Seeker</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">’</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">s Mark, you heal for half the damage it takes (rounded down).</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>Critical success</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You take necrotic damage equal to twice your Constitution modifier.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>Success</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The creature takes half damage. </span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>Critical failure</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The creature gains one level of exhaustion.</span> </li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":"HD: 2, Verbal"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"con","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["9d6","necrotic"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"con"},"requirements":"Bloodfussit","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"BIBjufHfbAOYdjrw"}
{"name":"Bloodspear Tier 2","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_blood.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You shoot forth a spear of your own blood at your foe. Make a ranged infusion attack against a target you can see within range. You must take 2d4 damage to yourself, and this damage cannot be reduced in any way (but it can be </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">taken from temporary hit points). On a hit, the target takes 2d10 necrotic damage.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><br /></span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>Critical Hit</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The target is sickened. A creature sickened by this ability suffers disadvantage on all Constitution saving throws. This effect lasts until the creature heals or otherwise recovers hit points.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":"Mana Pool: 1, Somatic"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":60,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"con","actionType":"rwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d10","necrotic"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"2d4","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"psionics"},"requirements":"Bloodfusist","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"DC0X9u0J5uy9M8f5"}
{"name":"Leech","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_blood.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You speak an elemental word and blood motes gather around your hand. Your touch siphons off a portion of the target's lifeforce to bolster your own vitality. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Select an ability score between Strength, Constitution, and Dexterity. The target must make a Constitution save or take 1d4 damage to this ability score, and your own score increases by this amount for the duration.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If your target bears your Seeker</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">’</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">s Mark and it fails its saving throw, you also heal as though you expended 1 Hit Die.</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>Critical success</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You take necrotic damage equal to twice your Constitution modifier as the motes backfire.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>Critical failure</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The target gains one level of exhaustion.</span> </li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":"Mana: 2, Mana Pool: 1, Verbal"},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"con","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4",""]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"con"},"requirements":"Bloodfusist","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"EfFmHurD3pVxEhSc"}
{"name":"Enervating Shot Tier 3","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_blood.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You cut your finger and with the blood, you fire a beam of energy that weakens the lifeforce of any creature it touches. Each creature in the line must make a Constitution save or gain 1 level of exhaustion and suffer 1d10 necrotic damage per Bloodweaving tier. If any of the targets bear your Seeker</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">’</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">s Mark, you recover hit points equal to your Constitution modifier.<br /></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>Critical success</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The creature is unaffected.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>Success</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The creature does not suffer exhaustion but still takes the necrotic damage.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>Critical failure</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The creature is stunned for 1 turn.</span> </li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":"Mana: 2. HD: 1, Somatic, Verbal"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":30,"width":5,"units":"ft","type":"line"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"con","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d10","necrotic"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"con"},"requirements":"Bloodfusist","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"FEqX03RRnwFF7fDK"}
{"name":"Infused Connection","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_hydro.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Hydrofusist are soothed by and attracted to water, allowing them to detect water sources up to 1 mile away and gain advantage on any skill and ability checks while in water.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"psionics"},"requirements":"Hydrofusist","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"GgTZavoyMQLGEAAO"}
{"name":"Flame Arrows Tier 3","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_pyro.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Fire motes transform ammunition (such as arrows, crossbow bolts, and sling stones) into fiery projectiles. Each piece of ammunition deals an extra 1d6 points of fire damage to any target it hits. A flaming projectile can easily ignite a flammable object or structure, but it won't ignite a creature it strikes. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Empower</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">While this ability is active, you can use a bonus action and spend 1 mana to turn your shot into a burst. Your shot deals damage as normal but also creates a burst of fire. All creatures within 10 feet of your target must make a Dexterity save or take 1d6 fire damage per Fireweaving tier you have mastered. </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Success</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Creatures take half damage.</span> </li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":"HD: 1, Somatic"},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"con","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d6","fire"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"con"},"requirements":"Pyrofusist","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"H1x0nDHjnfuSo7rQ"}
{"name":"Burning Stream Tier 3","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_pyro.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A 15-foot line of fire sprays from your outstretched, free hand. This ability remains active up to its duration so long as you maintain  concentration and keep one hand free. If you wield a weapon, shield, or perform any activity with the hand holding the burning stream, the infusion ends. This ability cannot function under water, but it can synergize with applicable infusions that utilize water. </span></p>\n<p><br /><span class=\"fontstyle0\">All creatures in the line must make a Dexterity saving throw or take 2d6 points of fire damage per Fireweaving tier and catch fire. A creature that catches fire takes fire damage at the start of each of its turns equal to your Constitution modifier up to the duration of this ability. This effect does not stack, and a creature can spend its action to extinguish the flames. Each round you continue to concentrate on this ability, you can select a new direction for the line to affect as a free action.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><br />Your stream sets fire to combustibles and damages objects in the area. It can melt metals with low melting points, such as lead, gold, copper, silver, and bronze. If the damage caused to an interposing barrier shatters or breaks through it, the stream may continue beyond the barrier if the area permits; otherwise it stops at the barrier.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><br /></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Empower</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If you expend 1 Hit Die, you can create a second line of fire using your other hand. If you overlap the lines, creatures in the overlap make their saving throw at Disadvantage, but don</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">’</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">t take damage from both lines. You may stop either line of fire at will on your turn, but once you stop maintaining a line, you must expend another Hit Die to recreate a line and only so long as the infusion is active. Your lines also make the area they affect difficult terrain, pushing against all creatures.</span> </p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":"Mana: 2, Mana Pool: 1, Somatic, Concentration"},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":15,"width":5,"units":"ft","type":"line"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"con","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["6d6","fire"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"con"},"requirements":"Pyrofusist","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"H7zCpZqpRkg3Sfm8"}
{"name":"Hard to Kill","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_blood.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You have advantage on death saving throws and on checks or saves against disease and illness.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"psionics"},"requirements":"Bloodfusist","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"I4B5w05wKO8zRKig"}
{"name":"Manipulate Water","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_hydro.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You must have a source of water within 10 feet of you to activate this ability (a pond, a filled waterskin, or falling rain). Once you have initiated this ability, you must stay within 30 feet of the water and hold concentration to continue controlling it.</span></p>\n<p><br /><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can create simple shapes and animate water that fits in a 5-foot cube. For example, you can create a solid orb of water that you shift and move up to 30 feet per turn. Once this ability ends, the water reverts back to its natural state, falling to the ground or being held in a prepared vessel.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Waterweaving Tier 2: </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\"> <span class=\"fontstyle0\">Your Manipulate Water improves. You can now control and move up to a 10-foot cube of water.</span></span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\"> <br style=\"font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;font-weight:normal;line-height:normal;text-align:-webkit-auto;text-size-adjust:auto\" /></span></strong></li>\n<li><strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Waterweaving Tier 3: </span></strong> <span class=\"fontstyle0\">Your Manipulate Water improves. You can now control and move up to a 20-foot cube of water.</span> </li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":"Mana Pool: 1, Somatic, Concentration"},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":30,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"psionics"},"requirements":"Hydrofusist","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"JK5xN8fEOH3f1yLu"}
{"name":"Whirlwind","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_aero.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Powerful winds coalesce to cause destruction in an area within 30 feet of you. You can trigger this ability only if you are outside or the ceiling is 80 feet or higher. The whirlwind is a cylinder that is 70 feet high with a radius of 20 feet. The area of the whirlwind is difficult terrain.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><br />All creatures in the area must make a Dexterity save or take 5d10 bludgeoning damage as powerful winds and debris buffet them. Flying creatures have disadvantage on this save unless they are Aerofusists. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Each turn you maintain concentration, you may move the whirlwind up to 15 feet in a straight line. Each creature the whirlwind moves through must make a Dexterity save. A creature can be affected by a whirlwind only once per turn. </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Critical Success: </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The creature is unaffected.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Success:</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The creature takes half damage.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Critical failure.</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The creature takes double damage and rises 20 feet into the air. While it is in the whirlwind, it remains aloft and must make a Dexterity (Acrobatics) check to move up to their movement speed in the difficult terrain. If they leave the whirlwind, they immediately fall.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><br /></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Synergy</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Using Hydrofusion or Bloodfusion abilities through the Whirlwind </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">increases their damage. These abilities passing through the whirlwind deal an additional amount of piercing damage equal to the fusist</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">’</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">s Constitution modifier. When an infusion attack misses its target (so long as it is not a critical miss), creatures within 5 feet of the target take piercing damage equal to the fusist</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">’</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">s Constitution modifier.</span> </p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":"HD: 2, Mana: 2, Mana Pool: 1, Somatic, Concentration"},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":20,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"radius"},"range":{"value":30,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["5d10","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"con"},"requirements":"Aerofusist","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"KQ3ncd1AjCi0240d"}
