{"_id":"pyWUta5hQx0IrMOu","name":"Detonating Mote","type":"feat","img":"systems/pergashaFoundryvtt/icons/pergasha_icons/infusion_pyro.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You use your lifeforce to condense fire motes into a bead of devastating potential and deploy it to a space you can see within range. You can either immediately detonate the bead or hold the bead ready up to a number of turns equal to your Constitution modifier. You determine how long to delay the detonation upon completing this ability and that time cannot change once it has been set unless someone touches the bead. If you choose a delay, the glowing bead sits at its destination until it detonates. A creature can pick up and hurl the bead as a thrown weapon (range 15 feet). If a creature handles and moves the bead within 1 turn of its detonation, there is a 25% chance that the bead detonates while being handled.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When the bead detonates, intense explosion triggers from the target location. The explosion is a 30-foot radius sphere that harms all creatures and objects in its range. All creatures in the area must make a Dexterity saving throw or take 10d6 fire damage and be knocked prone. The longer the bead waits to detonate, the more powerful it becomes. Each turn after creating it, the bead deals an additional 1d6 damage for each Fireweaving tier you master.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The explosion sets fire to combustibles and damages objects in the area. It can melt metals with low melting points, such as lead, gold, copper, silver, and bronze. If the damage caused to an interposing barrier shatters or breaks through it, the explosion may continue beyond the barrier if the area permits; otherwise it stops at the barrier.</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Critical fail</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The creature catch fire, taking your Constitution modifier in damage at the start of its next turn.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Success</strong>: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Creatures take half damage but do not fall prone.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Synergy</strong>: If you have an affinity to other infusions, you can enhance the bead. A bead can only withstand one synergy.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Aerofusion </strong>empowers the explosion. All creatures within the area of the explosion have disadvantage on their saving throw. In addition, creatures that are Huge or smaller are knocked prone regardless of the result of the saving throw (unless the creature is immune to being knocked prone).</li>\n<li><strong>Bloodfusion </strong>creates a toxic gas, sickening all creatures within the area of the explosion. Creatures are sickened, regardless of the result of the saving throw, and have a 1d4 penalty to all saving throws, ability checks, and attacks for 1 minute.</li>\n<li><strong>Hydrofusion </strong>turns your explosion of flames into a substance similar to lava. The ground affected by the explosion becomes difficult terrain and any creature entering an affected space or begins its turn in one takes 1d4 fire damage.</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":"HD: 4, Somatic"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":30,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"radius"},"range":{"value":100,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"dex","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["10d6","fire"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"con"},"requirements":"Pyrofusist","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DI11opiBN9KroioG":3},"flags":{}}
